An APC Chieftain, Tein Jack-Rich, has congratulated the president-elect and his running mate, Kashim Shettima, over their victory at the polls. Jack-Rich, who was a front line aspirant at the APC presidential primary that produced Tinubu said the president elect’s victory was well deserved. ‘In a congratulatory message, the politician expressed optimism that Tinubu and Shettima’s presidency will usher in a new dawn for Nigeria and promote inclusivity in governance for national good ‘I write on behalf of my wife, Dr. Mrs. Elizabeth Jack-Rich, Members of the Presidential Campaign Council from Rivers State, and the entire APC family in the state, to felicitate with you and the Vice President-Elect over your well-deserved victory in the just concluded presidential election in Nigeria,” he stated. Jack-Rich, who doubles as the Deputy director of the APC PCC fundraising committee, expressed confidence that Tinubu will preside over a peaceful and prosperous Nigeria given his enviable track record of hard work, devotion and dedication to He called for the cooperation and support of all Nigerians, including other candidates who contested the presidential election, to join hands with the President-Elect to build an egalitarian country that will work for all and sundry. According to him, now is the time to build bridges for the good of the country and not plot to tear it apart.